The Adamawa State Police Command has arrested and paraded 23 persons involved in rape and homosexual offenses in the state. Mr Olubenga Adeyanju, Commissioner of Police, who paraded the suspects in Yola said, 14 of them were involved in rape, while five of them including one Zainab Ja’afaru (female) 30 year-old was nabbed for abatement. Adeyanju said, Ja’afaru deceived her victim who happened to be her friend, to accompany her to Gerio in Jambutu to see her friend, unknown to her that it was organized plan against her. “Ja’afar on arrival, the gang leader invited his syndicate about nine and applied force on the victim and had sexual intercourse with her one after the other. The other four suspects were arrested for committing an offense against the order of nature comprising homosexual. The suspects were also engaged in homosexual and were constituting nuisance, to jabbi-lamba village before they were arrested. The CP pleaded with parents to desist from sending children at night to shops and malls to avert been raped. “Avoid sending your children to buy Maggi and salt in the dark”. the CP maintained. 